# See how I changed the original to say 200? Will that make them last longer?
# Answer: Yes, increasing the number of blinks to 200 will make the stars blink for a longer duration. With a delay of 0.5 seconds between each blink, the total duration will be approximately 100 seconds (200 blinks * 0.5 seconds per blink), which is more than a minute. If you want it to last exactly one minute, you can adjust the number of blinks or the delay time accordingly.

